  "conclusion": "Neither moving-average smoothing nor Kalman filtering substantially resolved the walking-vs-stationary confusion (walking recall: 54.2% \u2192 54.6%, best method: Kalman Tight (Q=0.5, R=10)). This confirms that the limitation is fundamental to centroid-only analysis at sub-3px/frame displacement magnitudes, where genuine slow walking is physically indistinguishable from tracker jitter."
